    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently, [`vim.lsp.buf.signature_help()`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html#vim.lsp.buf.signature_help()) takes a configuration parameter of type [`vim.lsp.buf.signature_help.Opts`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html#vim.lsp.buf.signature_help.Opts), which itself inherits from [`vim.lsp.util.open_floating_preview.Opts`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html#vim.lsp.util.open_floating_preview.Opts).\n\nThis parameter can be used to customize the window in which the signature help appears, but even though, [`vim.lsp.util.open_floating_preview.Opts`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html#vim.lsp.util.open_floating_preview.Opts) has a `title` field, [`vim.lsp.buf.signature_help()`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html#vim.lsp.buf.signature_help()) will ignore it and use the LSP server name as a title instead.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSetting the `title` field in [`vim.lsp.buf.signature_help.Opts`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html#vim.lsp.buf.signature_help.Opts) should overwrite the default title used by [`vim.lsp.buf.signature_help()`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html#vim.lsp.buf.signature_help()).\n\nAs far as I can tell, the change could be introduced [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/buf.lua#L410-L419):\n```lua\nlocal title = string.format('Signature Help: %s%s', client.name, sfx)\nif config.border then\n  config.title = title\nelse\n  table.insert(lines, 1, '# ' .. title)\n  if hl then\n    hl[1] = hl[1] + 1\n    hl[3] = hl[3] + 1\n  end\nend\n```\nThere are two cases to consider, bordered and non-bordered windows. In the case of bordered windows, I think it's sufficient to respect the supplied value of `title` and use a default value otherwise. In the case of non-bordered windows, however, I'd consider a special case when the user passes an empty string to request that no title is used. All in all, I think something like this could be used:\n\n```lua\nlocal default_title = string.format('Signature Help: %s%s', client.name, sfx)\nif config.border then\n  config.title = config.title or default_title\nelseif config.title ~= ''\n  table.insert(lines, 1, '# ' .. title)\n  if hl then\n    hl[1] = hl[1] + 1\n    hl[3] = hl[3] + 1\n  end\nend\n```\nOr even this:\n```lua\nconfig.title = config.title or string.format('Signature Help: %s%s', client.name, sfx)\nif not config.border and config.title ~= ''\n  table.insert(lines, 1, '# ' .. config.title)\n  if hl then\n    hl[1] = hl[1] + 1\n    hl[3] = hl[3] + 1\n  end\nend\n```\nsince I don't think that leaving the `title` field set is a problem when using non-bordered windows.\n\nIf you are ok with this, I can open a PR to implement it.",
